<item>
            <title>[LU-1038] osd: kernel panic after sanity test_103 starts</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-1038</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Kernel fails in panic during acceptance small test execution, right after start of sanity test_103.&lt;br/&gt;
Found in revision: ea44df63203b65de93e8aefe517059990296565c&lt;br/&gt;
Also observed in: 39b98cb351866da5648ea1a2216c108f8791226f&lt;br/&gt;
Console output excerpt below:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt; kernel:LustreError: 12800:0:(osd_handler.c:2416:osd_xattr_set()) ASSERTION((oh)-&amp;gt;ot_declare_xattr_set &amp;gt; 0) failed&lt;br/&gt;
 kernel:LustreError: 12800:0:(osd_handler.c:2416:osd_xattr_set()) LBUG&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The /var/log/messages in attachment. Though it doesn&apos;t include much useful info because of cache didn&apos;t get written on disk, unfortunately. &lt;/p&gt;</description>
